text.tspan: Daily production of calories per person
Daily per capita production does not measure the supply of kilocalories for human consumption because it does not
account for trade between countries, or allocation of foods towards other uses such as animal feed, biofuels and
wastage. It measures total production at the farm level.
Source: Hong et al. (2021). Global and regional drivers of land-use emissions in 1961–2017. Nature.
